    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-02-24T18:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-02-24T18:00:00-05:00" n="785"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d785">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">103.9169 Bogotá: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Colombia</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Lane</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Bogotá</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-02-24T18:00:00-05:00"
                            >February 24, 1944—6 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received February 25—12:56 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>320. For FEA.<note n="63" xml:id="d785fn63">Foreign Economic
                        Administration.</note> Reference is made to circular Airgrams of February
                        15<note n="64" xml:id="d785fn64">None printed except airgram dated February
                        15, 11:40 a.m., <ref target="#pg_653">p. 653</ref>.</note> proposing the
                    elimination from import recommendation procedure effective March 1 of five
                    groups of commodities. Upon receiving those proposals from the Embassy Dr. Diego
                    Mejia, head of the Office of Exchange and Export Control, immediately signified
                    his complete acceptance of and deep satisfaction with these and any other
                    proposals which may be forthcoming which will simplify the importation of
                    commodities from the United States. Under present Colombian policy no
                    independent national import controls are in effect or contemplated.</p>
                <p rend="center">. . . . . . . . . . . . . .</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lane</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
